<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-06-03T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-06-03T09:00:00-05:00" n="121" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d121">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51 W 89/2a: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Herrick</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-06-03T10:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">June 3,
                                        1922—10 a.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>Repeat following to Prague, Helsingfors, London, Budapest, Rome, Warsaw,
                            and Bucharest: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“Reference Department’s circular through Paris, dated April 21,
                                    noon, regarding World War Foreign Debt Commission. Report
                                    whether the Government to which you are accredited has appointed
                                    representatives, and when likely to arrive in Washington. It is
                                    desired that negotiations begin at an early date.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>